properties.sfomuseum:description: Handwritten letter from Harold M. Bixby to his wife, Debby Bixby, dated June 23, [1935] on stationery from the Manila Hotel; includes brief description of Mr. [C.S.] Russell who had been hired by Pan American Airways, John Steele, and Mr. Cushman; mentions Mr. Dai [Enki], Mr. [James] Ross, [Senator Manuel] Quezon, Governor General [Frank] Murphy, Bill [William] Pawley, Mrs. Norman Hill.
